title: The Great Rodeo Robbery
body:
Spider-Man and the Incredible Hulk

Simple fun.

  • Advertising supplement given away with various newspapers. Sponsored by Foley’s department stores.
  • Even with the none-too-subtle plugs for the department store, this is a fun read.
  • Having different villains for each hero helps.

6/10

summary: In the Spider-Man comics, Gwen Stacy is peters age and she dies (in HS). Then in the spiderverse storyline they introduced...
question: In the Spider-Man comics, Gwen Stacy is peters age and she dies (in HS). Then in the spiderverse storyline they introduced spider-Gwen who is from an alternate universe where she got spider powers and peter died. At that point peter and Gwen are both in their mid 20s, but spider Gwen was so popular she got her own series (and they showed her getting her powers as a teen). I guess for the spiderverse game they decided to have her younger. Comic universes like to fudge the age sometimes in reboots

blog.name: oxymitch
blog.title: Whatever Mitch
blog.description:
I am Mitch of Singapore, also an Ace. I enjoy reading superhero comics (especially Marvel); comic books aren't just for boys, girls read it too. However, I have no interest in any Marvel movie due to my jaded attitude, so I prefer Marvel cartoons like 90s X-Men TAS and Avengers EMH. 
Those Marvel comics I love reading are New Warriors, X-Men, Young Avengers, X-Factor, Avengers (not that Bendis era), Generation X, Avengers Academy and X-Force. 
Big fan of New Warriors and X-Men. 
My Favourite Marvel characters are...GAMBIT (Remy LeBeau), JUBILEE (Jubilation Lee), SPEEDBALL (Robbie Baldwin), WICCAN (Billy Kaplan), JUSTICE (Vance Astrovik), ROGUE (Anna Marie), SPEED (Tommy Shepherd), NIGHTCRAWLER (Kurt Wagner), FIRESTAR (Angelica Jones), QUICKSILVER (Pietro Maximoff), SHE-HULK (Jennifer Walters), QUASAR (Wendell Vaughn) and COSMO the space dog.

summary: Peter Parker and Robbie Baldwin - Same superhero job, different lifestyle.  Robbie Baldwin is a student and his superhero...
caption:
Peter Parker and Robbie Baldwin - Same superhero job, different lifestyle. 

Robbie Baldwin is a student and his superhero identity is Speedball. Robbie’s mother is a soap opera actress. Peter Parker’s superhero identity is Spider-Man and his civilian job at that time was a journalist photographer of Daily Bugle. Peter’s wife Mary Jane Watson-Parker was a fashion model and an actress. 

Also, both Spider-Man and Speedball are created by the late Steve Ditko. 

- New Warriors v1 #32, 1993
